page.title: 09St.Luke's church, Stickney.
page.content: Sunday School is taken by a lady every Sunday at 10.45 a.m.At Sunday School we learn about other people in other countries.Children up to the age of eleven go to Sunday School.When children reach the age of eleven they go to TYE group.TYE stands for"The Young Enthusiasts"and these young people meet at the church on a Sunday twice a month. They discuss problems and organize money raising events.They also take part in leisure activies such as canoeing camping and walking.Coffee mornings are held every Thursday in church ,and sometimees on Saturdays.
